            <h2 id="key-takeaways">Key Takeaways</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Chronic endometritis (CE) is a persistent, low-grade inflammation of the endometrial lining, typically caused by bacterial pathogens, and it is frequently subclinical.</strong> Most women with CE have no dramatic symptoms. That is part of why it goes undetected, per <a href="/library/chronic-endometritis-potential-cause-of-infertility-and-obstetric-and-neonatal-c-recard0poglnf8sx1/">Kitaya et al. 2015</a>.</li>
